[SN]TITLE[SN]
Accrington Stanley: Steven Hewitt joins and Terry Gornell signs new deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Accrington Stanley have signed midfielder Steven Hewitt on a one-year deal and agreed a new two-year contract with striker Terry Gornell.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Hewitt, 22, had been on trial with the League Two side following his release by Burnley this summer.
He made just three substitute outings for the Clarets after coming through their academy.
Gornell, 26, returned to Stanley in February 2015 from Cheltenham for his second stint with the club.
The forward started his career at Tranmere and has also had spells at Shrewsbury and Rochdale.
